<subpara id="RM000000PFU01KX_08" type-id="51" category="05" proc-id="RM0250U___00002R100000">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten4>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Read freeze frame data using an intelligent tester. The ECM records vehicle and driving condition information as freeze frame data the moment a DTC is stored. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can be helpful in determining whether the vehicle was running or stopped, whether the engine was warmed up or not, whether the air-fuel ratio was lean or rich, as well as other data recorded at the time of a malfunction (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000PDS00ZX"/>).</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>The throttle actuator current (THROTTLE MOT) and the throttle actuator duty ratio (THROTTLE OPN / THROTTLE CLS) can be read using the intelligent tester. However, the ECM shuts off the throttle actuator current when the ETCS malfunctions.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten4>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000PFU01KX_09" type-id="01" category="01">
